Paper Code: ETEC-205
Paper: Switching Theory & Logic Design


UNIT- I
Number Systems and Codes:
  Decimal, Binary, Octal & Hexadecimal Number systems, Codes- BCD, Gray Code, Excess-3 Code, ASCII, EBCDIC, Conversion between various Codes.
Switching Theory:
  Boolean Algebra- Postulates and Theorems, DeMorgan’s Theorem, Switching Functions- Canonical Forms- Simplification of Switching Functions- Karnaugh Map and Quine Mc-Clusky Methods.
Combinational Logic Circuits:
  Review of basic gates- Universal gates, Adder, Subtractor ,Serial Adder, Parallel Adder- Carry Propagate Adder, Carry Look-ahead Adder, Carry Save Adder, Comparators, Parity Generators, Decoder & Encoder, Multiplexer & De-multiplexer, ALU, PLA and PAL.
[T2,T3]

UNIT- II
Integrated circuits:
  TTL & CMOS logic families and their characteristics.
  Brief introduction to RAM & ROM.
Sequential Logic Circuits:
  Latches & Flip Flops- SR, D, T & MS-JK Flip Flops, Asynchronous Inputs.
Counters and Shift Registers:
  Design of Synchronous & Asynchronous Counters- Binary, BCD, Decade & Up/Down Counters, Shift Registers, Types of Shift Registers, Counters using Shift Registers- Ring Counter & Johnson Counter.
[T2,T3]

UNIT- III
Synchronous Sequential Circuits:
  State Tables State Equations and State Diagrams, State Reduction and State Assignment, Design of Clocked Sequential Circuits using State Equations.
  Finite state machine- capabilities and limitations, Mealy & Moore models- minimization of completely specified and incompletely specified sequential machines, Partition techniques and merger chart methodsconcept of minimal cover table.
[T1]

UNIT- IV
Algorithmic State Machine:
  Representation of sequential circuits using ASM charts synthesis of output and next state functions, Data path control path partition-based design.
Fault Detection and Location:
  Fault models for combinational and sequential circuits, Fault detection in combinational circuits.
  Homing experiments, distinguishing experiments, machine identification and fault detection experiments in sequential circuits.
[T1]


Text Book:
[T1] Zyi Kohavi
      “Switching & Finite Automata Theory”, 2nd Edition
       TMH
[T2] Morris Mano
      "Digital Logic and Computer Design”
       Pearson
[T3] R.P. Jain,
      “Modern Digital Electronics”, 2nd Edition
       TMH

Reference Books:
[R1] A Anand Kumar
      “Fundamentals of Digital Logic Circuits”
       PHI
[R2] Taub, Helbert and Schilling
      “Digital Integrated Electronics”
       TMH